%I A395160 #25 May 15 2026 21:13:21
%S A395160 1,1,2,2,1,3,3,4,4,4,1,5,3,5,3,3,6,6,4,7,7,4,4,8,8,8,1,9,9,13,10,10,6,
%T A395160 11,5,5,11,6,6,12,12,4,13,5,13,7,7,14,6,6,14,8,15,15,24,16,16,1,17,7,
%U A395160 7,17,9,9,18,12,18,13,19,19,10,10,20,8,8,20,6,21,21,32,22,22,6,6,23,32,23
%N A395160 Irregular triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the average of the odd numbers of the k-th 2-dense sublists of divisors of n and of its conjugate, with n >= 1, k >= 1.
%C A395160 For the definition of "conjugate" see A237270.
%C A395160 Conjecture 1: row lengths give A237271.
%F A395160 Conjecture 2: T(n,k) = (A384226(n,k) + A384226(n,m+1-k)) / 2, where m = A237271(n) is the row length.
%F A395160 Conjecture 3: T(n,k) = A237270(n,k) / A038712(n) = A237270(n,k) * A000593(n) / A000203(n).
%e A395160 Triangle begins:
%e A395160   1;
%e A395160   1;
%e A395160   2, 2;
%e A395160   1;
%e A395160   3, 3;
%e A395160   4;
%e A395160   4, 4;
%e A395160   1;
%e A395160   5, 3, 5;
%e A395160   3, 3;
%e A395160   6, 6;
%e A395160   4;
%e A395160   7, 7;
%e A395160   4, 4;
%e A395160   8, 8, 8;
%e A395160   1;
%e A395160   ...
%e A395160 For n = 78 we have:
%e A395160 List of divisors of 78 ..............................................: [1, 2, 3, 6,    13, 26, 39, 78].
%e A395160 2-dense sublists of divisors ........................................: [1, 2, 3, 6 ], [13, 26, 39, 78].
%e A395160 Odd numbers in the 2-dense sublists of divisors .....................: [1,    3    ], [13,     39    ].
%e A395160 Sum of the odd numbers in the 2-dense sublists of divisors ..........: [      4    ], [        52    ].
%e A395160 Sum of the odd numbers in the conjugates ............................: [     52    ], [         4    ].
%e A395160 Sum of the odd numbers in the 2-dense sublists and of its conjugates : [     56    ], [        56    ].
%e A395160 Average .............................................................: [     28    ], [        28    ].
%e A395160 So the 78th row of the triangle is [28, 28].
%Y A395160 Row sums give A000593.
%Y A395160 Row n is a palindromic composition of A000593.
%Y A395160 Row n of A237270 is a palindromic composition of A000203.
%Y A395160 Row n of A237593 is a palindromic composition of A005843.
%Y A395160 Row n of A384222 is a palindromic composition of A000005 (conjectured).
%Y A395160 Row n of A384225 is a palindromic composition of A001227.
%Y A395160 Cf. A038712, A174973 (2-dense numbers), A237271, A379288, A384149, A384226.
%K A395160 nonn,tabf,new
